ocr_text: Get higher returns Instantly! citibank ‘UNIT LINKED INSURANCE PLAN (ULIP) IS LIFE INSURANCE SOLUTION THAT PROVIDES FOR THE BENEFITS OF RISK PROTECTION AND FLEXIBILITY IN INVESTMENT. THE INVESTMENT IS DENOTED AS UNITS AND IS REPRESENTED BY THE VALUE THAT IT HAS ATTAINED CALLED AS NET ASSET VALUE (NAV). THE POLICY VALUE AT ANY TIME VARIES ACCORDING TO THE VALUE OF THE UNDERLYING ASSETS AT THE TIME. IN A ULIP, THE INVESTED AMOUNT OF THE PREMIUMS AFTER DEDUCTING FOR ALL THE CHARGES AND PREMIUM FOR RISK COVER UNDER ALL POLICIES IN A PARTICULAR FUND AS CHOSEN BY THE POLICY HOLDERS ARE POOLED TOGETHER TO FORM A UNIT FUND. A UNIT IS THE COMPONENT OF THE FUND IN A UNIT LINKED INSURANCE POLICY. THE RETURNS IN A ULIP DEPEND UPON THE PERFORMANCE OF THE FUND IN THE CAPITAL MARKET. ULIP INVESTORS HAVE THE OPTION OF INVESTING ACROSS VARIOUS SCHEMES, LE, DIVERSIFIED EQUITY FUNDS, BALANCED FUNDS, DEBT FUNDS ETC. IT IS IMPORTANT TO REMEMBER THAT IN A ULIP, THE INVESTMENT RISK IS GENERALLY BORNE BY THE INVES- TOR. IN A ULIP, INVESTORS HAVE THE CHOICE OF INVESTING IN A LUMP SUM (SINGLE PREMIUM) OR MAKING PREMIUM PAYMENTS ON AN ANNUAL, HALF-YEARLY, QUARTERLY OR MONTHLY BASIS. INVESTORS ALSO HAVE THE FLEXIBILITY TO ALTER THE PREMIUM AMOUNTS DURING THE POLICY'S TENURE. FOR EXAMPLE, IF AN INDIVIDUAL HAS SURPLUS FUNDS, HE CAN ENHANCE THE CONTRIBUTION IN ULIP. CONVERSELY AN INDIVIDUAL FACED WITH A LIQUIDITY CRUNCH HAS THE OPTION OF PAYING A LOWER AMOUNT (THE DIFFERENCE BEING ADJUSTED IN THE ACCUMULATED VALUE OF HIS ULIP), ULIP INVESTORS CAN SHIFT THEIR INVESTMENTS ACROSS VARIOUS, PLANS/ASSET CLASSES (DIVERSIFIED EQUITY FUNDS, BALANCED FUNDS, DEBT FUNDS) EITHER AT A NOMINAL OR NO COST.

ocr_text: Coffee witha conscience... Maria Araceli Reyes, , works as a Farm Manager for the Caficultores de Morazan Cooperative, known as CAFEMOR. “It was especially bad five years ago as the coffee price at market was so low — nobody could live on the coffee and whole plantations were completely lost. Now, though, things will be different.” “We were only able to achieve all of this by working together. That's why we formed the Maria Araceli Reyes, Farm Manager othing kick starts the day better than a N steaming mug of coffee. And a good meal wouldn't be complete without that cup of rich roasted flavour. But behind every cup of coffee, there's a story — and the story of NESCAFE Partners’ Blend is one of hope... A quick lesson in coffee growing... e problem for coffee producers has always been that their livelihood is directly linked to the coffee bean price on the world’s markets. If that price drops (as it has in recent years) the growers, and their families, suffer. And should the coffee crop fail for any reason, they've nothing to fal! back on. Small wonder then that so many farmers have given up the struggle to grow coffee.  Working together to make a difference ESCAFE Partners’ Blend is NESCAFE's first Fairtrade coffee and truly embraces the three pillars of sustainability: economic, social and environmental. In El Salvador the NESCAFE Partners’ PARTNERS’ BLEND cooperative to see how we could move things forwards together. Advisors helped us to organise ourselves and find other alternatives to survive.” Blend project is working with four cooperatives: agronomists from NESCAFE help the farmers improve their yield with up-to-date technology and modern, sustainable farming practices. These improvements have helped the farmers to produce some of the finest arabica beans available. In addition they are guaranteed a fair price for their harvest. The NESCAFE agronomists also advise on supplementary planting such as banana and citrus fruit to help protect the farmers against the economic risk of coffee crop failure. The income generated along with support from NESCAFE has helped improve the every day lives not only for the farmers and their families. The project has helped with diversification opportunities as well as providing some educational and other materials for local children. And the new clinic has a doctor that visits regularly. What about the coffee? And what becomes of the premium quality arabica beans grown on these farms? Every one is roasted and blended by SOCIETE DES PRODUITS NESTLE SA, VEVEY, SWITZERLAND TRADE MARK OWNER the experts at NESCAFE to produce a coffee that’s exceptionally, “rich, smooth and well balanced”... Partners’ Blend. So, the next time you're in the supermarket choosing your jar of coffee, stop for a second. Do you just want a great tasting, quality coffee? Or do you want a great tasting, quality coffee that's helping the people in some of the poorest regions of the planet to a better, sustainable future?
